"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Each phase of the myocardial action potential (numbers, upper panel) corresponds to a deflection or interval on the surface electrocardiogram (lower panel). Phase 4, the resting membrane potential, is responsible for the TQ segment; this segment has a prominent role in the ECG manifestations of ischemia during exercise testing.",
